  <main>

    <!-- What is this -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">What Is This Site</div>
      <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:#333;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:.9rem;">
        This is Jacob Rickey's personal portfolio site and a live demonstration of the Azure IaC project built
        for ITS 5900-120 (Cloud Systems) at Ohio University. The site itself <em>is</em> the project —
        it runs on the infrastructure it documents.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:#333;line-height:1.7;">
        Nothing is deployed manually. Every change goes through <code>tofu apply</code> to provision infrastructure
        and <code>ansible-playbook</code> to configure it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Stack + Security -->
    <div class="row">

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Tech Stack</div>
        <div class="stack-row">
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Hosting</span><span class="stack-val">Azure (South Central US)</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Provisioning</span><span class="stack-val">OpenTofu (IaC)</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Configuration</span><span class="stack-val">Ansible</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Web server</span><span class="stack-val">nginx · TLS 1.3 only · HSTS</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">TLS cert</span><span class="stack-val">Let's Encrypt (auto-renew)</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">DNS</span><span class="stack-val">Cloudflare + Azure DNS zone</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Secrets</span><span class="stack-val">Azure Key Vault</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">State</span><span class="stack-val">Azure Blob Storage (locked)</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">AI interface</span><span class="stack-val">MCP over Streamable HTTP</span></div>
          <div class="stack-item"><span class="stack-label">Self-healing</span><span class="stack-val">sentinel + systemd timer</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Security Choices</div>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li><strong>No passwords anywhere.</strong> SSH uses Ed25519 keys only. DB password is auto-generated by OpenTofu and stored in Key Vault — never typed.</li>
          <li><strong>DB has no public IP.</strong> The only path in is through the app VM (bastion pattern), enforced at both NSG and network layer.</li>
          <li><strong>TLS 1.3 only.</strong> No TLS 1.2 fallback. One-year HSTS with preload.</li>
          <li><strong>Minimal attack surface.</strong> <code>server_tokens off</code> hides nginx version. Security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy) on every response.</li>
          <li><strong>Rate-limited AI endpoint.</strong> The Ask Claude feature is capped per IP and globally to prevent abuse and cost overrun.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- What is MCP -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">What Is MCP</div>
      <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:#333;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:.9rem;">
        MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open standard that lets AI models call tools running on external servers.
        Think of it like a plugin system for Claude — the server exposes named tools with defined inputs and outputs,
        and Claude decides when to call them based on what a user asks.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:#333;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:.9rem;">
        This site runs one MCP server (<code>mcp-infra</code>) on the app VM. It exposes two tools:
        <code>sentinel_log</code> (reads the service health log) and <code>write_activity</code> (logs each session
        to the activity feed on the project page).
      </p>
      <div class="note">
        Claude runs on Anthropic's infrastructure, not on this VM. The VM calls the Claude API, Claude chooses which
        tools to invoke, and only sees the data the tools return. The MCP server itself has no access to secrets or
        the database — it can only read a log file and write to a JSON file.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">MCP / Streamable HTTP</span>
        <span class="tag">FastMCP</span>
        <span class="tag">read-only tools</span>
        <span class="tag">Anthropic API</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Ask Claude + Cost -->
    <div class="row">

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">The Ask Claude Feature</div>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:#333;line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:.8rem;">
          The Ask Claude box on the <a href="/projects/cloud/" style="color:#0078d4;">project page</a> lets visitors
          ask questions about the infrastructure. It works like this:
        </p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Your question is POSTed to <code>/ask</code> on this server.</li>
          <li>A FastAPI app sends it to the Claude API with a system prompt describing the infrastructure.</li>
          <li>If the question is about service health, Claude calls the <code>sentinel_log</code> MCP tool to read live data.</li>
          <li>The answer is returned to your browser and logged to the activity feed.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="note">
          The endpoint is rate-limited: 10 questions per IP per day, 150 globally per day.
          This keeps API costs predictable.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Cost &amp; Sustainability</div>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:#333;line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:.8rem;">
          The site is currently running on Ohio University Azure credits. When those run out, the plan is to migrate to
          a personal Azure subscription using the free and low-cost tiers.
        </p>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li><strong>VMs:</strong> Standard_B2pts_v2 ARM64 — cheapest general-purpose tier, ~$14/month each.</li>
          <li><strong>AI costs:</strong> Claude Haiku at ~$0.77/day maximum (150 calls × ~600 tokens output).</li>
          <li><strong>Migration path:</strong> Static hosting (Cloudflare Pages / GitHub Pages) for the landing page + Azure Functions for <code>/ask</code> if VMs are shut down.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Links -->
